<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08122</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT STRENGTHENING THE NATIONAL FOOD AUTHORITY (NFA) AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : States that the National Food Authority shall be classified as a Government Instrumentality vested with Corporate Powers (GICP), tasked to maintain safe, adequate and continuous supply, at reasonable prices of food grains in the country.
Intends to address various challenges and concerns facing the National Food Authority such as: the reasonableness and affordability of prices of staple rice and corn; enforceability of rules and regulations governing grains business; licensing and registration of all rice and corn business
Defines several terms among others such as “adulteration”, “contumacy”, “farm gate price”, “food security”, “Minimum Access Volume (MAV)”; and “National Rice Reserve”. 

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SAVELLANO, DEOGRACIAS VICTOR B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-16</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-09-06)</td><td>2. Bravo (M.) (000 2018-09-25)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT ENTERPRISES AND PRIVATIZATION ON 2018-10-10</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON AGRICULTURE AND FOOD, FOOD SECURITY</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PREVIOUS COMMITTEE REFERRALS :PRIMARILY REFERRED TO AGRICULTURE AND FOOD on 2018-08-28;</td></tr></table>